SIMPLE: downward
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Downward
<hw>Down"ward</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Downward
<hw>Down"ward</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moving or extending
from a higher to a lower place; tending toward the earth or its center,
or toward a lower level; declivous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With <qex>downward</qex> force⟦br⟧
That drove the sand along he took his way.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Descending from a head, origin, or source; <as>as, a
<ex>downward</ex> line of descent</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Tending to a lower condition or state; depressed;
dejected; <as>as, <ex>downward</ex> thoughts</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir P.
Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Downweed</ent>⟦br⟧
